#*: She attended all our guests, most rigorously insisted on '''uncloaking''' and unshawling them, whether they would or not; {{...}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To remove one's cloak.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1826|first=Allan|last=Cunningham|title=Paul Jones: A Romance|volume=2|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=fHn-wJG36iQC&pg=PA38|page=38|passage=Nay, but my fireside's not the deckâ€”I am mistress here; so let me '''uncloak''' thee." She seized his cloak, and, not without a slight resistance on his part, unclasped the collar, and threw it aside.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|science fiction}} To become [[visible]] again by turning off a [[cloaking device]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2011|first=David|last=Mack|title=Rise Like Lions|series=Star Trek: Mirror Universe|passage=Don't try to target the Klingons as they '''uncloak''', you won't have time. Just use the phasers to make a nofly zone between us and the Takagi.}}

